President Donald Trump has invited several guests to attend his address to a Joint Session of Congress. These guests include John and Megan Crowley, whose daughter was diagnosed with Pompe disease and is now a sophomore at the University of Notre Dame. Jessica and Sheila Gregory, whose daughter has spina bifida and is planning for college and a career as a public interest reporter. Denisha Merriweather, who struggled with coursework as a child but went on to graduate from high school and college. Jessica Davis and Susan Oliver, who are the widows of police officers killed in the line of duty by an illegal immigrant. Carryn Owens, the widow of a Navy SEAL who died in a mission in Yemen. Maureen McCarthy Scalia, the widow of late Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia. And Jamiel Shaw Sr., whose son was tragically shot by an illegal immigrant in 2008.